<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,1887,1984]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,282,1888,1912]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
We studied material of this species from 
<collectingCountry box="[740,852,1887,1911]" name="Mongolia" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[862,961,1888,1912]" name="Hungary" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Hungary</collectingCountry>
, the Mediterranean region and 
<collectingCountry box="[1306,1435,1887,1911]" name="Cape Verde" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Cape Verde</collectingCountry>
islands. Variablity of this species is not large and for this reason we propose synonymization of 
<taxonomicName box="[1260,1436,1924,1948]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capverdensis">
<emphasis box="[1260,1436,1924,1948]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">S. capverdensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName box="[207,365,1960,1984]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pinguiculus">
<emphasis box="[207,365,1960,1984]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">S. pinguiculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
